8:
Uh-oh. Let me guess. Your last partner 
wasn't quite up to scratch either?
10:
I mean... They weren't BAD or anything, 
you know? We just didn't click, that's 
all.
13:
I feel I must inform you, Ellya... This is 
the ninth person you've gone through 
this month.
14:
You may be the Starlight 
Sharpshooter, but perhaps it's about 
time you loosened up your 
requirements.
18:
Okay, well... Being strong is a must, 
obviously. I'll need someone who can 
come back with me in one piece.
21:
And intelligence is just as important, 
right? Someone who can see eye-to-
eye with me and my vision.
23:
Not to mention age. I've got pretty big 
ambitions for myself, so I need to 
know if I can build a future with them.
26:
A person who knows how to chill, you 
know? Like, not some hothead 
obsessed with conquering the 
Kaleidoscope.
30:
Oh, and they should be someone who 
inspires me!
33:
Someone like that can't be THAT hard 
to find, right? I mean, as long as 
they're around my level, that's good 
enough for me!
35:
Well, according to the criteria you just 
listed, there are zero people in the 
guild I can introduce to you.
41:
Would you consider a veteran 
adventurer? You have quite the 
reputation among those operating in 
the midways.
43:
I mean, that's flattering and all, 
but I'm tryin' to shake things up with 
some new blood, you know?
47:
Hey. What about those guys over 
there?
49:
Ah, you mean the ones Lilie 
introduced recently? We don't have 
too much information on them, 
so I can't—
52:
Yes... they might be the inspiration 
I've been looking for!
57:
Hi there! You guys adventurers, 
by any chance?
59:
I'm Ellya, by the way. Pleased to 
meetcha! Cool if I join you for a bit?
66:
I'll keep it short. I'm looking for 
someone to conquer 
the Kaleidoscope with me. 
How about it?
70:
The hell are you goin' on about? 
We just met. You have too much to 
drink or something?
74:
Not at all! I'm not just some nobody, 
I'll have you know. Surely you're 
familiar with... the Starlight 
Sharpshooter?
79:
Wait, I've heard of you! You hold the 
record for reaching the Midways faster 
than anyone on record!
81:
And not only that, you almost always 
choose to work alone rather than 
form a party!
84:
You've got that part twisted. 
See, it's not that I WANT to work alone 
or anything. But nobody's been able 
to keep up with me so far.
88:
Then why choose my—er, why choose 
our crew?
94:
What the hell, Ellya? 
Is this some kind of joke?
98:
Not only did you turn me down... 
Now I see you tryin' to party up with 
these newbies!
100:
Listen, Ash. I hate to break it to you, 
but you're just not ready for the 
Depths—
102:
I don't wanna hear it! If you think 
you're such hot stuff, 
how about we go right now?
105:
Sorry, you guys. Mind if I take care of 
something real quick?
112:
I'm going to fire a light orb at you. 
You can choose to try and dodge it or 
take it head-on. Your call.
114:
If you're still able to fight, I'll reconsider 
your skills. Ready?
117:
Ready? Pfft... I was BORN ready! Don't 
think for a second that I'm the same 
Ash from before—
121: Soul of luster, locked and loaded!
128:
Sorry, Ash. Truth is, if you think this 
hurts, the monsters in the depths can 
and will do a lot worse.
131:
Heh... Hopefully, that knocked some 
sense into him.
137:
So! Have you given my invitation 
anymore thought?
143:
Let's just say I've got an eye for these 
things. The moment I saw you, I knew 
you were special!
145:
Just by looking at your faces, I can 
tell... You guys have SEEN some things.
149:
I dunno about that... What do you 
think, Nimbus?
153:
Eh, why not? Never hurts to have 
some more muscle in our ranks.
156:
But this is a two-way street. 
If you wanna join us, you'll have to do 
things our way too. 
You still good with that?
160:
Yup! Sounds like we have ourselves 
a deal, uh... Sorry, what's your name?
165: I'm Alk. Nice to have you with us, Ellya.
169:
Likewise! Now let's go kick that 
Kaleidoscope's ass!
